{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb9caa665-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1395ss–1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1395ss–1"},"text":"§ 1395ss–1.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Clarification","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any health insurance policy that provides reimbursement for expenses incurred for items and services for which payment may be made under title XVIII of the Social Security Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1395"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 1395","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] but which are not reimbursable by reason of the applicability of deductibles, coinsurance, copayments or other limitations imposed by a Medicare Advantage plan (including a Medicare Advantage private fee-for-service plan) under part C of such title ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1395w–21"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 1395w–21","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] shall comply with the requirements of section 1882("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"tail":") of the such "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002946"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002946"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original."}],"tail":" Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1395ss"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 1395ss","children":[],"tail":"("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"tail":"))."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb9caa666-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/275/tI/s104/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–275, title I, § 104(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-07-15"},"text":"July 15, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/2502"},"text":"122 Stat. 2502","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb9caa667-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb9caa668-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idb9caa669-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Social Security Act, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"act Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/620"},"text":"49 Stat. 620","children":[],"tail":". Title XVIII of the Act is classified generally to this subchapter. Part C of title XVIII of the Act is classified to section 1395w–21 et seq. of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1305"},"text":"section 1305 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idb9caa66a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Medicare Improvements for Patients and Providers Act of 2008, and not as part of the Social Security Act which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
